article.headline: Eastern Michigan 75, Ohio 64
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. (AP) -- Markus Austin scored 26 points to lift Eastern Michigan to a 75-64 win over Ohio on Wednesday. Austin hit six of nine shots from behind the 3-point line to help the Eagles (12-12, 6-9 MAC) stay in contention for a first-round home game in the Mid-American Conference tournament. Jaivon Harris scored 21 points on 8-of-16 shooting from the field to lead Ohio (9-17, 6-9). After the Eagles took a 36-31 halftime lead, the Bobcats managed to go up 45-43 before Eastern Michigan answered with a 14-2 run to grab a 57-47 lead with 9:33 left. A layup by Austin with 3:41 to go in the game gave the Eagles their biggest advantage at 68-53. Eastern Michigan shot 50.9 percent from the field and held the Bobcats to just 40.3 percent shooting. Seeds four through eight will host a first-round game in the MAC tournament, which begins March 8. After Wednesday's game, Eastern Michigan was in a four-way tie with Marshall, Ohio and Akron for the eighth-best record in the conference. <
